des: "For Super BowlÂ® one year, I really wanted to make jalapeno poppers but wasn't in the mood for all the work so I put this dip together. It combines all of the flavors of a jalapeno popper and has become a request at every football party we throw, as well as one of my husband's favorite dips."
ins: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and Parmesan cheese together in a saucepan over low heat until evenly blended. Fold in bread crumbs, jalapeno peppers, and red pepper flakes. Cook and stir dip until Parmesan cheese is melted, 2 to 5 more minutes.
